videos.description: Michigan  turns it over with the 24-second violation..
videos.headline: Stifling Purdue D forces the Michigan shot clock violation.

videos.description: Color broadcaster Dan Dakich talks to his son Michigan guard Dan Dakich on senior day.
videos.headline: Dan Dakich interviews his son Andrew on Senior Day

videos.description: D. Walton Jr. makes the steal, cues the break, and lays it in on the other end.
videos.headline: Derrick Walton Jr with the steal and fantastic finish on the other end

videos.description: Caleb Swanigan spins in the post and slams it home.
videos.headline: Purdue's Caleb Swanigan with the spin and slam

videos.description: Wolverine's Moritz Wagner scores 22-points on 9-of-12 shooting, 3-of-6 from long range in 1st half.
videos.headline: Wolverine's Wagner scores 22-points in the first half

videos.description: Caleb  Swanigan turns it over off the double team.
videos.headline: Swarming Michigan defense forces Swanigan turnover

videos.description: Carsen Edwards feeds to Isaac Haas for the slam
videos.headline: Boilermakers' Haas throws down the slam

videos.description: Derrick Walton Jr. drives to the basket, absorbs the contact and puts it in.
videos.headline: Wolverine's Walton Jr.  takes defender off the dribble and floats it in

videos.description: Derrick Walton Jr beats the shot clock with the three.
videos.headline: Derrick Walton Jr. hits step-through three as shot clock expires.

videos.description: Derrick Walton Jr. discusses the emotional win over Purdue in his last game at the Chrysler Center on senior day.
videos.headline: Postgame interview with Michigan senior Derrick Walton Jr.

videos.description: Moe Wagner scores 22 of his 24 points in the first half to propel Michigan to an 82-70 win over No. 14 Purdue, snapping the Boilermakers' six-game winning streak.
videos.headline: Wagner leads Michigan past Purdue
